# Usage

Start with these tokens when customizing articles:

- `--article-content-max-width` and `--article-content-max-width-mobile` for readable line length
- `--article-title-*` tokens to control title typography, spacing, and alignment
- `--article-authors-*` and `--article-abstract-*` to style metadata slots
- `--article-toc` and `--article-toc-title` to toggle and label the table of contents

Article tokens focus on the container and its major slots (title, authors, abstract, content, references). Content blocks inside the article still use their own node tokens (paragraphs, headings, figures, etc.).

# Tokens

## Layout Tokens

Control the overall article width and responsive sizing.

| Token                              | Description                                   | Default Value                    |
| ---------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------- |
| `--article-content-max-width`      | Max width for article content blocks          | `var(--content-width)`           |
| `--article-content-max-width-mobile` | Max width for article content on mobile     | `var(--content-width-mobile)`    |

## Title Tokens

Typography and layout for the article title slot.

| Token                              | Description                                      | Default Value                          |
| ---------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------ | -------------------------------------- |
| `--article-title-font-family`      | Font family for the article title               | `var(--heading-font-family)`           |
| `--article-title-font-size`        | Title font size                                  | `calc(var(--text-font-size) * 2.5)`    |
| `--article-title-font-size-mobile` | Title font size on mobile                        | `calc(var(--text-font-size-print) * 2.0)` |
| `--article-title-font-size-print`  | Title font size in print                         | `calc(var(--text-font-size-print) * 2.0)` |
| `--article-title-font-weight`      | Title font weight                                | `var(--font-weight-bold)`              |
| `--article-title-line-height`      | Title line height                                | `var(--line-height-tight)`             |
| `--article-title-line-height-mobile` | Title line height on mobile                    | `var(--line-height-tight)`             |
| `--article-title-letter-spacing`   | Letter spacing for the title                     | `-0.02em`                              |
| `--article-title-color`            | Title text color                                 | `var(--text-color-primary)`            |
| `--article-title-text-align`       | Title text alignment                             | `center`                               |
| `--article-title-max-width`        | Max width for the title block                    | `calc(var(--article-content-max-width) * 0.9)` |
| `--article-title-margin-bottom`    | Space below the title block                      | `var(--space-8)`                       |

## Authors Tokens

Typography and spacing for the authors slot.

| Token                              | Description                                      | Default Value               |
| ---------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------ | --------------------------- |
| `--article-authors-font-size`      | Authors font size                                | `var(--text-font-size)`     |
| `--article-authors-color`          | Authors text color                               | `var(--text-color)`         |
| `--article-authors-text-align`     | Authors text alignment                           | `left`                      |
| `--article-authors-margin-bottom`  | Space below the authors block                    | `var(--space-6)`            |

## Abstract Tokens

Styling for the abstract slot and its background.

| Token                              | Description                                      | Default Value               |
| ---------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------ | --------------------------- |
| `--article-abstract-font-size`     | Abstract font size                               | `var(--text-font-size)`     |
| `--article-abstract-color`         | Abstract text color                              | `var(--text-color)`         |
| `--article-abstract-background`    | Abstract background color                        | `var(--surface-background)` |
| `--article-abstract-text-align`    | Abstract text alignment                          | `left`                      |
| `--article-abstract-max-width`     | Max width for abstract content                   | `var(--article-content-max-width)` |
| `--article-abstract-margin-bottom` | Space below the abstract block                   | `var(--space-6)`            |

## Table of Contents Tokens

Configuration for the automatic article table of contents.

| Token                              | Description                                         | Default Value |
| ---------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------- | ------------- |
| `--article-toc`                    | TOC mode (`none`, `true`, or heading depth 1-6)     | `none`        |
| `--article-toc-title`              | TOC heading text                                    | `"Contents"`  |

# Examples

## Default Article

Standard article styling with the base layout and title treatments:

```css
:root {
  /* No design token overrides */
}
```

::: style

```html raw
<stencila-article>
  <section slot="title">
    <h1>Modeling coastal ecosystems under changing climates</h1>
  </section>
  <section slot="authors">
    <p>Jordan Hayes, Priya Natarajan, and Emilio Vargas</p>
  </section>
  <section slot="abstract">
    <stencila-heading><h1>Abstract</h1></stencila-heading>
    <stencila-paragraph>
      <p slot="content">We present a coupled hydrodynamic and ecological model that improves predictive accuracy for nutrient cycling in estuarine systems.</p>
    </stencila-paragraph>
  </section>
  <section slot="content">
    <stencila-paragraph>
      <p slot="content">The model integrates tidal fluxes with species-level responses to temperature, producing stable forecasts across seasonal regimes.</p>
    </stencila-paragraph>
  </section>
</stencila-article>
```

:::

## Editorial Title Treatment

Larger, left-aligned title with tighter tracking and centered authors:

```css
:root {
  --article-title-text-align: left;
  --article-title-font-size: calc(var(--text-font-size) * 3);
  --article-title-letter-spacing: -0.03em;
  --article-title-max-width: var(--article-content-max-width);
  --article-authors-text-align: center;
}
```

::: style --article-title-text-align: left; --article-title-font-size: calc(var(--text-font-size) * 3); --article-title-letter-spacing: -0.03em; --article-title-max-width: var(--article-content-max-width); --article-authors-text-align: center;

```html raw
<stencila-article>
  <section slot="title">
    <h1>Field notes from the edge of the ice</h1>
  </section>
  <section slot="authors">
    <p>Marina Cho and Luca Romano</p>
  </section>
  <section slot="content">
    <stencila-paragraph>
      <p slot="content">This report documents daily observations gathered during the 2024 polar expedition, with a focus on sea ice melt and microbial activity.</p>
    </stencila-paragraph>
  </section>
</stencila-article>
```

:::

## Abstract Callout and TOC

Highlight the abstract and enable a short table of contents:

```css
:root {
  --article-abstract-background: var(--surface-sunken);
  --article-abstract-text-align: justify;
  --article-abstract-max-width: calc(var(--article-content-max-width) * 0.95);
  --article-toc: 3;
  --article-toc-title: "On this page";
}
```

::: style --article-abstract-background: var(--surface-sunken); --article-abstract-text-align: justify; --article-abstract-max-width: calc(var(--article-content-max-width) * 0.95); --article-toc: 3; --article-toc-title: "On this page";

```html raw
<stencila-article>
  <section slot="abstract">
    <stencila-heading><h1>Abstract</h1></stencila-heading>
    <stencila-paragraph>
      <p slot="content">We introduce a new sampling method for long-term climate archives that reduces uncertainty in sediment-derived temperature reconstructions.</p>
    </stencila-paragraph>
  </section>
  <section slot="content">
    <stencila-heading><h2>Methods</h2></stencila-heading>
    <stencila-paragraph>
      <p slot="content">Core samples were extracted from five coastal sites and processed using standardized isotope ratios for calibration.</p>
    </stencila-paragraph>
  </section>
</stencila-article>
```

:::

# Tips

**Readable width**: Adjust `--article-content-max-width` first, then tune `--article-title-max-width` for balance.

**TOC depth**: Use `--article-toc: 3` (or any 1-6 value) to keep the contents concise.

**Metadata alignment**: Match `--article-title-text-align` with `--article-authors-text-align` for a unified header.
